com.huawei.ipr.pof.gui.console

Class ConsoleUI

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.huawei.ipr.pof.gui.console.ConsoleUI
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class ConsoleUI
extends java.lang.Thread
    A command line console UI for POF Controller. User could input commands to control POF Controller and switches via this console UI.

    the command format is as:
          OPCMD OPTYPE PARAMETER1 PARAMETER2 ...

    OPCMD include:
          DISPLAY (or DIS), ADD, DELETE (or DEL), MODIFY, RESET, SET, SAVE, LOAD, HELP, ABOUT, VERSION, EXIT

    OPTYPE include:
          PROTOCOL, METADATA, SWITCH, PORT, TABLE, ENTRY (or FLOWENTRY/FLOW), GROUP, METER, COUNTER, ALL

    Command format:

    DISPLAY PROTOCOL             //display all protocols
    DISPLAY PROTOCOL ALL       //display all protocols
    DISPLAY PROTOCOL -1         //display metadata
    DISPLAY PROTOCOL 2         //display one protocol[id=2]
    DISPLAY METADATA           //display metadata

    DISPLAY SWITCH               //display all switch's all information
    DISPLAY SWITCH ALL         //display all switch's all information
    DISPLAY SWITCH 11223344 //display the switch(id=11223344)'s information

    DISPLAY PORT                 //display all switches' all tables' all ports' information
    DISPLAY PORT ALL           //display all switches' all tables' all ports' information
    DISPLAY PORT 11223344.ALL       //display switch(id==11223344)'s all ports' information
    DISPLAY PORT 11223344.2         //display switch(id==11223344)'s one port(id==2)'s information

    DISPLAY TABLE                 //display all switches' all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY TABLE ALL           //display all switches' all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY TABLE 11223344.ALL   //display switch(id==11223344)'s all tables' information
    DISPLAY TABLE 11223344.10     //display switch(id==11223344)'s table(id==10)'s information

    DISPLAY ENTRY               //display all switches' all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY ALL             //display all switches' all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY 11223344           //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY 11223344.ALL     //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all tables' all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY 11223344.10       //display the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10)'s all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY 11223344.10.ALL //display the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10)'s all flow entries
    DISPLAY ENTRY 11223344.10.2     //display the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10)'s one flow entry(id=2)

    DISPLAY GROUP               //display all switches' all group entries
    DISPLAY GROUP ALL             //display all switches' all group entries
    DISPLAY GROUP 11223344           //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all group entries
    DISPLAY GROUP 11223344.ALL     //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all group entries
    DISPLAY GROUP 11223344.3       //display the switch(id=11223344)'s group entry(id=3)

    DISPLAY METER               //display all switches' all meters
    DISPLAY METER ALL             //display all switches' all meters
    DISPLAY METER 11223344           //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all meters
    DISPLAY METER 11223344.ALL     //display the switch(id=11223344)'s all meters
    DISPLAY METER 11223344.5       //display the switch(id=11223344)'s meters(id=5)

    DISPLAY COUNTER 11223344.6             //display the switch(id=11223344)'s counter's(id=6) value

    DISPLAY ALL                   //display all information include metadata/protocols/switches/tables/entryies/gourps/meters



    ADD PROTOCOL MAC dmac.48 smac.48 etype.16   //add a new protocol, with its name(MAC) and the fields (name.length)
    ADD METADATA mf1.16 mf2.8             // add new metadata elements (name.length) on the tail of the metadata list

    ADD TABLE 11223344 Acl MM 100 4.6.a1.8.3     //add a new table in switch(id=11223344), the table is a 100 entry in maximal, MM (MaskedMatch) type OFTableType, with name Acl. the table has five match fields (fields id are: 4, 6, metadata named a1, 8 and 3)

    ADD ENTRY 11223344.10 0 1.0.0 3.0889.ffff INS=APPLY_ACTIONS(SET_FIELD.3.0777.ffff$CALCULATE_CHECKSUM.1.2.3.4);GOTO_TABLE.10.0;
                        //add a new flow entry in switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10), the entry's priority=0, match_file_value1=[fieldid=1,value=0,mask=0], match_file_value2=[fieldid=3,value=0x0889,mask=0xffff], contain two instructions (use ";" to separate), ins1 is an APPLY_ACTIONS OFInstructionType, ins2 is a GOTO_TABLE OFInstructionType, the APPLY_ACTIONS GOTO_TABLE contains two actions (use "$" to separate), action1 is a SET_FIELD OFActionType, with three parameters (3.0777.ffff); action2 is a CALCULATE_CHECKSUM OFActionType, with four parameters (1.2.3.4); the GOTO_TABLE instruction with two parameters (10.0)

    ADD GROUP 11223344 ALL SET_FIELD.4.1111.ffff CALCULATE_CHECKSUM.1.2.3.4 OUTPUT.5.0.0.0
                        //add a new group entry in switch(id=11223344), the OFGroupType OFGroupMod.OFGroupType is ALL, the action list contains three actions: SET_FIELD, SET_FIELD, OUTPUT

    ADD METER 11223344 32               //add a new meter in switch(id=11223344) with the rate is 32 kbps



    MODIFY PROTOCOL 2 dmac.48 smac.48 etype.16       //modify a existed protocol[id=2], with the new fields (name.length)
    MODIFY METADATA mf11.32 mf22.64             //modify the metadata list using the new metadata elements (name.length)

    MODIFY ENTRY 11223344.10.2 0 1.0.0 3.0889.ffff INS=APPLY_ACTIONS(SET_FIELD.3.0777.ffff$CALCULATE_CHECKSUM.1.2.3.4);APPLY_ACTIONS(OUTPUT.5.0.0.0)
                        //modify a existed flow entry(id=2) in switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10), with new parameters

    MODIFY GROUP 11223344.3 ALL SET_FIELD.fid.hex_v.hex_m CALCULATE_CHECKSUM.1.2.3.4 OUTPUT.5.0.0.0
                        //modify a existed group entry(id=3) in switch(id=11223344), with new parameters

    MODIFY METER 11223344.5 64               //modify a existed meter(id=5) in switch(id=11223344) with new rate is 64 kbps



    DELETE PROTOCOL 2             //delete a existed protocol[id=2]

    DELETE TABLE 11223344.ALL       //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s all empty tables
    DELETE TABLE 11223344.10       //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10), if the table(id=10) is not empty, it will not be deleted.

    DELETE ENTRY 11223344.10.ALL       //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10)'s all entries.
    DELETE ENTRY 11223344.10.2         //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s table(id=10)'s one entries(id=2).

    DELETE GROUP 11223344.ALL       //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s all groups.
    DELETE GROUP 11223344.3         //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s one group(id=3).

    DELETE METER 11223344.ALL       //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s all meters.
    DELETE METER 11223344.5         //delete the switch(id=11223344)'s one meter(id=5).



    SET PORT ALL true               //set all switches' all ports' openflow enable
    SET PORT 11223344 enable   //set switch(id=11223344)'s all ports' openflow enable
    SET PORT 11223344.all false   //set switch(id=11223344)'s all ports' openflow disable
    SET PORT 11223344.2 disable   //set switch(id=11223344)'s port(id=2)'s openflow disable



    RESET COUNTER 11223344.6           //reset the switch(id=11223344)'s counter(id=5)'s value=0



    SAVE filename.db           //save database into a filename.db


    LOAD filename.db yes           //load database from filename.db and write OFMessages to switches
    LOAD filename.db no           //load database from filename.db and do NOT write OFMessages
    LOAD finename.pofscript     //load console script from a finename.pofscript



    ABOUT           //print version information


    VERSION       //print version information


    HELP             //print help information

      • addEntry

        private boolean addEntry(java.util.List<java.lang.String> cmdList,
               int curCmdListIndex)
        add a new entry.

        format:
        ADD ENTRY switchid.globalTableId priority f1id.hex_value.hex_mask f2id.hex_v.hex_m metadataName.hex_v.hex_m ... fnid.hex_v.hex_m INS=OFInstructionType1.para1.para2.para3;OFInstructionType2.para1.para2.para3;...

        if instruction is an action, OFInstructionType2.para1.para2.para3 part should be: APPLY_ACTIONS(OFActionType1.para1.para2.para3$OFActionType2.para1.para2.para3)

        Use ";" to separate instructions;
        Use "$" to separate actions;

        e.g.:
        ADD ENTRY 11223344.10 0 1.0.0 3.0889.ffff INS=APPLY_ACTIONS(SET_FIELD.fid.hex_v.hex_m$CALCULATE_CHECKSUM.1.2.3.4);GOTO_TABLE.10.0;APPLY_ACTIONS(OUTPUT.5.0.0.0)

        Parameters:
        cmdList -
        curCmdListIndex -
        Returns:
        success or fail
